<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="31" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d31">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">
                            <persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1">Leahy</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head>No. 31 <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_THS1" type="from">Truman</persName> to Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CMWS1" type="to">Churchill</persName>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d31fn1">Sent to the United States Naval
                                Attaché, London, via Navy channels.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-22">22 May 1945</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Number 46, personal and top secret, from the President to the Prime
                            Minister.</p>
                        <p>I am asking Mr. <persName corresp="#p_DJE1">Joseph E. Davies</persName>
                            to come to see you prior to the pending conference between you,
                                <persName corresp="#p_SMIV2">Marshal Stalin</persName> and myself.
                            There are a number of matters that I want him to explore with you and
                            which I would prefer not to handle by cable. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_DRK1">Davies</persName> will be in London probably the
                            twenty-fifth. I would appreciate it if you could see him at your
                            convenience.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_THS1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Truman</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>